DataElement.preferredName: Blood Specimen Cell Isolation Aliquot Prepared Number
DataElement.preferredDefinition: Number of blood specimen aliquots prepared of the isolated cells.

DataElementConcept.preferredName: Blood Specimen Cell Isolation Aliquot Preparation
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: A small volume of blood removed for testing or storage._Any of various processes to isolate one or more specific cell populations from a heterogeneous mixture of cells._Pertaining to a portion of the whole; any one of two or more samples of something, of the same volume or weight._The act or process of making something ready.

Concepts.definition: A small volume of blood removed for testing or storage.

Property.preferredDefinition: Techniques and methods for separating cells (usually viable) based on a variety of criteria for separation, such as size or density, non-specific surface properties, or specific surface properties.  Examples include cell affinity chromatography and centrifugation using density gradients.:Pertaining to a portion of the whole; any one of two or more samples of something, of the same volume or weight.:The act or process of making something ready.

Concepts.definition: Any of various processes to isolate one or more specific cell populations from a heterogeneous mixture of cells.
Pertaining to a portion of the whole; any one of two or more samples of something, of the same volume or weight.
The act or process of making something ready.

ConceptualDomain.preferredDefinition: A practiced and regimented skill or series of actions.
